user.biography: Within everything there lies an enigma, the question is whether it should be sought out and revealed, for there is always more than meets the eye...

nodes.caption:
Learn to love everyone, we're all equal and no one individual is better or worse than others, we all have an equal time to live, the difference between individuals is how they chose to spend that time, who they meet, who they trust…

Trust not all but a few, not everyone shares the same mindset as you, some may be jealous, some may be selfish or maybe not, some may want to see you succeed, some may want you be the best possible version of yourself, it is these individuals that you trust, these individuals want to success but won't turn their backs on you when you fail. They help you get back on your feet, and after failure, as you know, comes success.

It's painful to know that some people find joy in your failure but knowing that failure prepares you for success, they in some way, help you.

One concept that remains constant is never doing wrong to someone else, no matter how much you dislike them, forgive them and forget, the other person may be experiencing a multitude of different emotions/situations you have no idea about perhaps because they don't trust you. So let them be and remember, do wrong to none.

Like and comment below your thoughts 👇

It does not help oneself being enthralled by fantasies where hardships, inconveniences, heart breaks and disappointments are non-existent, causing one to forget to forge a life. A life  where failure, struggles, time and learning make dreams come true. A life imperfectly perfect…

Nothing will ever be as perfect as dreams, but that’s what makes it perfect. The future will forever remain unpredictable while dreams will not.

By looking at something you will only see the surface, what you see, perceive will change how you view that something forever. You may “look” at a painting and view various brush strokes forming numerous shapes and a blend of colours, compare this to what you may “see”; an unparalleled marvel expressed by the artist, a constitution of a story to touch the mind, body and souls of all who may “see” it for what it truly is.

Remind yourself to always be the last to speak, remember that there’s something to learn in everything and that if you speak you won’t learn anything, so listen until you’ve exposed yourself to all the teachings there possibly are. Don’t be a fool and give in to a compulsion to speak, be wise and listen, learn from those with the wisdom and soon you’ll become a conduit spreading that knowledge whilst others will listen.

First learn, then teach.

You will never know the future but you definitely will know the present, learn to live in this present and not in your future; if you spend too much time dreaming on your perfect life, how you will you ever get there?

Instead focus on your goals, know your opportunities, reach out to those already successful and learn from them. You’ll never know your future, for the possibilities of what you may be are endless.

Don’t wait around for opportunities or the motivation to start, you must be your own push force, the only way you will get anything in life is if you work for it, and to do that you need to get started. Stop waiting around. Work for what you want, get learning, build on what you know and you’ll be the best at what you do.

Get ahead of the game. Get started.

Knowledge is one of the main building blocks of success, the more experiences you have the greater your chances are of succeeding in whatever you may pursue. Sure you may fail from time to time, but within failure comes knowledge, within knowledge comes experience and with experience comes success - this is the best ‘interest’ you may ever receive.

So invest time in learning something new, invest time in pursuing your passion and dream career - you will never get anywhere with money alone, knowledge is the new currency so invest in it; invest in you!

This is an interesting quote that can be interpreted in many different ways, one way is the psychological aspect of how we view our ability to complete tasks, for example having a fixed mindset which focuses on your inability to complete a task and/or unwillingness to improve and grow this makes you procrastinate as you focus on the task not being completed, however simply adhering to a growth mindset allows you to create a motivational and productive mentality, focusing on learning how to complete the task instead of why you cannot.

Changing your mindset is the first step to killing procrastination.

Like and comment how you're going to complete that job you've been putting off 👇

Failing is an interesting concept, learning from failures is significantly more beneficial than not trying, ignoring the possibility to try is essentially refusing to learn and for the most part you have nothing to lose but an exceptional amount of experience to gain.

Many people think failure as something that is to be ashamed of or a negative thing but that's something that's wrongly perceived. Failure is a process which helps us to improve and practice upon our experiences. How are we supposed to crawl before we can walk?

Let your failures be your own path and journey to success, it’s the rest from travelling in such rapid and tiring pace that you need to stop and pause to have a rest and go back to your usual pace.

Ask yourself how failure has shaped you and leave a comment on what you have learned from your failures?

Happiness is the elusive state of positivity, well-being and satisfaction with letting go of the trouble of the past, looking forward to what the future holds for you and of course being at peace with the present. The moments in life that made you smile should never be regretted, for they shape you in ways you aren’t even aware of.

So what makes you smile? Appreciation of where you are? Love of a special someone? Well being and satisfaction? Having peace of mind? Your success within projects and other endeavours? Your friends? Your family? Or is it just the state of being alive?

Comment below what makes you happy 😊

Don’t waste your precious time waiting around for something to come by because who knows when that will happen.

Build your opportunities by defining exactly what you want because without this realisation, you won’t notice the opportunities. You are the force for your future, waiting around for something justs slows that down to the point at which it could never happen!

So get to work finding what you want, recognise the opportunities and if the opportunity doesn’t come knocking, BUILD ONE! For every moment that passes an opportunity sails by.
